Ross COYNE, Appellee, v. THE Steamtug MAPLELEAF, Appellant, and THE Barge FIDELITY, Appellee. No. 355. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. May 11, 1936. Single & Tyler, of New York City (Wilbur H. Hecht, of New York City, of counsel), for appellant. Purdy & Purdy, of New York City (Frank C. Mason, of New York City, of counsel), for libelant-appellee. Courtland Palmer, of New York City (Francis J. Ryan, Jr., of New York City, of counsel), for appellee The Fidelity.

Before L. HAND, SWAN, and CHASE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decree affirmed.
